<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17470909-19">
               <interp inst="t17470909-19" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470909-19" type="year" value="1747"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470909-19" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17470909"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470909-19" type="date" value="17470909"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17470909-19-off80-c128" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470909-19-defend156 t17470909-19-off80 t17470909-19-verdict83"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17470909-19-off80-c129" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470909-19-defend158 t17470909-19-off80 t17470909-19-verdict82"></join>
         
               <p>333, 334. 
               
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-defend156" type="defendantName">
                     Samuel 
                     Waring 
                  <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend156" type="surname" value="Waring"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend156" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend156" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-defend158" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Sudger 
                  <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend158" type="surname" value="Sudger"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend158" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-defend158" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             were indicted, for <rs id="t17470909-19-off80" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-off80" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-off80" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing four Deal Boards value 2 s. and three Deal Joists value 2 s.
            </rs> the Property of 
               <persName id="t17470909-19-victim159" type="victimName">
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-victim159" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470909-19-off80 t17470909-19-victim159"></join>
                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t17470909-19-cd81" type="crimeDate">July the 25th</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470909-19-off80 t17470909-19-cd81"></join>.</p>
               <p>Q to 
               <persName id="t17470909-19-person160">
                  John 
                  Gardener 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person160" type="surname" value="Gardener"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person160" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person160" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Do you know the Prisoners at the Bar, what have you to alledge against them?</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174709090011"></xptr>Gardener. This hither one, Waring, I catch'd carrying away some Boards; four Deal Boards, belonging to the Parish of Cripplegate and St Luke's. I have often detected them, and they were flinging a Brick at me. I caught him with four Boards coming up from the Alley.</p>
               <p>Q Do you know, whether he had them from the Houses belonging to the Parish?</p>
               <p>Gardener. It was from that House by his own Confession.</p>
               <p>Q. What did he say?</p>
               <p>Gardener. He said he had them from the old Houses in our Parish.</p>
               <p>Q Where are they situated?</p>
               <p>Gardener. In Gun yard.</p>
               <p>Q Who was along with Waring?</p>
               <p>Gardener. Surgon was along with him, and he went and followed the others, and this Fellow throw'd them down, and was like to throw them down upon our Common Council-man's Leg.</p>
               <p>Q. Who is Surgon ?</p>
               <p>Gardener. He is not taken.</p>
               <p>Q. to 
               <persName id="t17470909-19-person161">
                  Oliver 
                  Hunt 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person161" type="surname" value="Hunt"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person161" type="given" value="Oliver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person161" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Do you know the Prisoner at the Bar?</p>
               <p>Hunt I saw Waring with the Boards upon his Shoulder, and just as he came at my Door, Mr Gardener call'd out, Stop him, Stop that Rogue. I leap'd out in order to stop him; I had not got three Yard but he threw the Board down and ran away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person162">
                  Thomas 
                  Jackson 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person162" type="surname" value="Jackson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person162" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person162" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am Constable. I took up Waring, and he own'd he was guilty in stripping this House. He own'd it before Justice Bellamy, and he committed him.</p>
               <p>Q Have you any Thing to say against Sudger ?</p>
               <p>Jackson I have a List of Half a Score that have done a great deal of Damage.</p>
               <p>Q. to 
               <persName id="t17470909-19-person163">
                  Thomas 
                  Holland 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person163" type="surname" value="Holland"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person163" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person163" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . What have you to say on the Behalf of the Prisoner Waring?</p>
               <p>Holland. I have known him twelve Years. I never knew him wrong Man, Woman, or Child; I take him to be an honest Lad.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person164">
                  Mary 
                  Cobb 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person164" type="surname" value="Cobb"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person164" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person164" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known Waring's Parents for five and twenty Years.</p>
               <p>Q. How long have you known him?</p>
               <p>This Witness, who aim'd to be more abundant in Character than the rest, she answer'd, That she knew him before his Birth, and that he was born of honest Parents.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person165">
                  Anne 
                  Spillman 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person165" type="surname" value="Spillman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person165" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person165" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He has frequently work'd with my Husband, and none can give him an ill word?</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person166">
                  Anne 
                  Simmonds 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person166" type="surname" value="Simmonds"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person166" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person166" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known him seven or eight Years, and I never knew him to wrong any body.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person167">
                  Jane 
                  Hutchinson 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person167" type="surname" value="Hutchinson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person167" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person167" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He has the Character of a very honest Lad.</p>
               <p>Q. to Mr Gardener. Are these Houses lock'd up?</p>
               <p>Gardener. They have been fenc'd up with double Deal. They have done a great deal of Damage. I have a few Houses hard by. I have lost a pretty deal of Leaden Pipe. &amp;c.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17470909-19-person168">
                  John 
                  Sudger 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person168" type="surname" value="Sudger"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person168" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person168" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             
                  <rs id="t17470909-19-verdict82" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-verdict82" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>, 
               <persName id="t17470909-19-person169">
                  Samuel 
                  Waring 
               <interp inst="t17470909-19-person169" type="surname" value="Waring"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person169" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-person169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             
                  <rs id="t17470909-19-verdict83" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-verdict83" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17470909-19-punish84" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-punish84" type="punishmentCategory" value="miscPunish"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470909-19-punish84" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="branding"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470909-19-defend156 t17470909-19-punish84"></join>
               
                     <note>[Branding. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
